      577.75,
      575.23,
      712.54
    ],
    "text": "The low pressure area located northeast of the Sri Lanka, still persist. This system is expected to move away from Sri Lanka during the next 48 hours according to the latest weather analysis based on May 14th morning. Under the influence of this system, wind speed and rainy conditions over the sea areas around the island may increase in the coming days. The naval and fishing communities are requested to be attentive to the future forecasts and bulletins issued by the Department of Meteorology in this regard. Condition of Rain:",
